description:
Let me start by saying my dinner was good, and the prices are excellent here. However, when I came in with four friends for dinner our service was so deplorable  I will never return. My general theory on dining out is as follows; 

If the dinner is mediocre, but the service is friendly and accomodating, I will always return. However, even if the food is delicious, and the service is horrid - I will never go back. 

The experience at Citrus Club fit the latter of the two, where our waitress was so rude it was nearly comical. It began with one friend and I sitting down at our table, while the other couple was next-door buying a bottle of wine. The waitress asked us where the rest of our party was, and upon explanation that they were simply 2 doors down (at most, 3 minutes away) she told us we had 2 minutes or we had to, "get out." I cannot make this stuff up! We were speechless, and the couple at the table next to us leaned over to ask if they really just overheard that exchange. Unbelievable! Needless to say, our friends arrived momentarily, and the servers attitude did not change. It's unfortunate, as the dinner was pretty good, and the prices are fantastic.
